Package com.intersys.globals.graphapi.globalsgraphdb

Interface Summary
GlobalsNodeSubscript GlobalsNodeSubscript is a marker interface used to help the GlobalsDB Graph API employ GlobalsDB subscripts to establish persistent graphs among global nodes.
 

Class Summary
GlDictionary presents a set of parameters for mapping a graph into a GlobalsDB database
GlFlag A GlFlag is used to mark values of globals with known strings
GlGraph GlGraph is an implementation of the Graph package that uses the GlobalsDB free database as persistence.
GlGraphComponent implementation class for graph component, extends hashmap
GlGraphEdge GlGraphEdge implements the Graph API using the GlGraphNode as the base node.
GlGraphNode Implements a Graph node by embedding the GlobalsDB type 'NodeReferenceImpl' Note that other GraphComponent implementors extend the GlGraphComponent directly; this will not work for GlGraphNode because its GraphNode interface (Collection) conflicts with the Map interface used by GlGraphComponent.
GlGraphPath GlGraphPath implements the Path interface for GlobalsDB graphs
GraphAPIEnv this is a collection of utility objects and functions for making use of the globals graph api
StringGlobalsSubscript Implements a Globals subscript using a single string
